WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.320
There will be organizing beams.

2
00:00:02.560 --> 00:00:07.400
Inside, these beams, in relation to the small wing here.

3
00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:08.460
Beams here.

4
00:00:09.780 --> 00:00:12.380
You see, these are very important lines of force.

5
00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:17.000
But the moment you have primitive cephalic flexion,

6
00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:20.700
you will have the sub-mesencephalic mesenchyme

7
00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:24.660
which will compress between the anterior part of the cerebral vesicle

8
00:00:24.660 --> 00:00:27.000
and the posterior cerebral vesicle.

9
00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:27.940
That's at the beginning.

10
00:00:28.070 --> 00:00:29.210
My tissue is like this.

11
00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:31.330
And by the flexion movement,

12
00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:33.670
I move forward.

13
00:00:34.410 --> 00:00:35.750
The mesenchyme underneath,

14
00:00:35.830 --> 00:00:37.870
it will undergo a compression field on its axis

15
00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:42.170
It will lose water,

16
00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:43.990
it will densify and it becomes

17
00:00:43.990 --> 00:00:45.270
a cartilaginous tissue.

18
00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:48.070
This is how the base of the skull is formed.

19
00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:50.150
By the flexion movement.

20
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:52.770
With as an axis, always,

21
00:00:53.730 --> 00:00:54.410
my notochord.

22
00:00:54.670 --> 00:00:55.910
And on either side,

23
00:00:56.140 --> 01:01:2.560
I have what is called at the very top the ethmoid, just below

24
01:01:2.560 --> 01:03:60
the body of the sphenoid,

25
01:03:540 --> 01:06:960
even further down the basilar part of the occipital bone,

26
01:07:240 --> 01:11:460
and especially here what are called the wings of the sphenoid,

27
01:11:660 --> 01:14:680
but also the point where the eye will rest.

28
01:16:140 --> 01:18:280
It's the support of the eye, the sphenoid.

29
01:18:460 --> 01:21:500
The sphenoid is very important for the stability of the eye.

30
01:21:500 --> 01:24:140
The moment it grows, the mesenchyme...

31
01:24:211 --> 01:25:791
which is above, the bony

32
01:26:531 --> 01:27:531
capsule of the eye,

33
01:27:811 --> 01:30:251
will develop through the development

34
01:30:251 --> 01:32:491
of the brain, around the eye.

35
01:33:531 --> 01:34:191
So the eye

36
01:34:191 --> 01:36:331
becomes there, it follows

37
01:36:331 --> 01:38:31
the movement, it is conformer

38
01:38:31 --> 01:38:871
and conformed,

39
01:40:811 --> 01:42:391
and the bone tissue

40
01:42:391 --> 01:44:371
comes to engrave around, comes to close

41
01:44:371 --> 01:46:291
with specific lines of force

42
01:46:291 --> 01:48:291
that support the eye's support.

43
01:48:291 --> 01:50:91
That means the eye can destabilize the skull

44
01:50:91 --> 01:52:121
or the skull can destabilize the eye.

45
01:52:281 --> 01:54:121
or the skull can destabilize the eye.

46
01:54:741 --> 01:55:721
You see?

47
01:55:721 --> 01:58:261
A small blow, a small fringe

48
01:58:261 --> 02:0:161
can completely destabilize the orbit

49
02:0:941 --> 02:2:421
and completely destabilize

50
02:2:421 --> 02:3:761
the reflection, you see?

51
02:3:761 --> 02:6:161
So it's really important to be able

52
02:6:161 --> 02:8:221
to restabilize the eye, to understand it

53
02:8:221 --> 02:10:321
both through the brain and through

54
02:10:321 --> 02:12:241
the skull. This is your nose.

55
02:13:161 --> 02:14:201
It's going to grow.

56
02:14:361 --> 02:16:61
Boom! And there, we see the eye appear

57
02:16:61 --> 02:18:81
on the side. And you see,

58
02:18:161 --> 02:20:181
at the same time, I have the palate system

59
02:20:351 --> 02:22:511
being formed. The moment I have

60
02:22:511 --> 02:24:491
my eye being formed,

61
02:24:611 --> 02:26:431
my palate is being put in place.

62
02:26:831 --> 02:28:131
You see?

63
02:28:131 --> 02:30:171
Really with the closure. The palatine,

64
02:30:171 --> 02:32:91
here, which is placed. And when I have

65
02:32:91 --> 02:34:151
completely my eye that has found its

66
02:34:151 --> 02:36:311
axis in its verticality,

67
02:36:411 --> 02:37:791
in its horizontality,

68
02:38:11 --> 02:39:811
I have the palate formed.

69
02:40:271 --> 02:41:951
So it's really the terminal point

70
02:41:951 --> 02:42:651
terminal

71
02:43:991 --> 02:46:331
very important on the bone level that is formed.

72
02:46:571 --> 02:48:171
It's a first convergence

73
02:48:422 --> 02:52:562
So we see here, you see, the growth, the importance of this growth.

74
02:52:782 --> 02:55:262
And look at the cephalic part.

75
02:55:602 --> 02:59:122
It is when this cephalic part will really begin to grow

76
02:59:122 --> 03:1:802
that the eyes come closer to the median line.

77
03:1:902 --> 03:5:502
Look closely, with a fulcrum that will be at the level of the nasion.

78
03:9:362 --> 03:10:822
Now look at the white part.

79
03:15:182 --> 03:16:62
I'm growing.

80
03:17:572 --> 03:19:12
Now, I explode.

81
03:22:292 --> 03:24:432
The eyes return to the median line.

82
03:30:292 --> 03:31:872
Did you see?

83
03:32:612 --> 03:34:552
We see this biodynamics again

84
03:34:552 --> 03:36:432
or this morphogenesis of development.

85
03:39:952 --> 03:42:112
This enormous growth

86
03:42:912 --> 03:44:412
that comes through here.

87
03:45:502 --> 03:48:22
which makes my eyes come to the center.

88
03:49:462 --> 03:54:182
Cortical development guides the eye into its position.

89
03:54:462 --> 03:56:82
You will have two spirals.

90
03:57:202 --> 03:58:802
An eye spiral

91
04:0:342 --> 04:4:402
and a bony counter-spiral.

92
04:6:302 --> 04:8:442
You see that in the shape of the sutures.

93
04:8:602 --> 04:12:522
If you look closely, you have to study the orientation of this suture.

94
04:12:633 --> 04:16:133
And you see that this pre-maxilla is three-dimensional.

95
04:18:413 --> 04:19:453
You see, it does this.

96
04:20:253 --> 04:24:693
You see, it goes up, it goes down and it goes up again.

97
04:24:913 --> 04:26:593
And it really creates a three-dimensionality.

98
04:26:933 --> 04:33:993
And well, you see that it forms, this shape, orbital, ocular.